&lt;p&gt;For the first time in years, I &lt;em&gt;really&lt;/em&gt; miss being in my high school marching band. I can't handle the amount of nostalgia this video is making me feel&lt;sup id="fnref:a"&gt;&lt;a class="footnote-ref" href="#fn:a" rel="footnote"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/sAzzbrFgcUw?autohide=1&amp;amp;fs=1&amp;amp;autoplay=0&amp;amp;iv_load_policy=3&amp;amp;rel=0&amp;amp;modestbranding=1&amp;amp;showinfo=0&amp;amp;hd=1" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;

&lt;div class="footnote"&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li id="fn:a"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And the amount of jealousy I feel towards towards my sister, who was at the game and saw this in person.&amp;#160;&lt;a class="footnote-backref" href="#fnref:a" rev="footnote" title="Jump back to footnote 1 in the text"&gt;&amp;#8617;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</summary></entry><entry><title>Hydrogen Cars: A Dream That Won't Die</title><link href="http://jayhickey.com/2012/10/hydrogen-cars" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2012-10-09T11:44:00-04:00</updated><author><name></name></author><id>tag:jayhickey.com,2012-10-09:2012/10/hydrogen-cars</id><summary type="html">&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Automakers are showing new interest because key problems with fuel cellsâ€”their limited capacity to convert hydrogen to electricity and their susceptibility to freezingâ€”have largely been overcome in recent years. At the same time, the first mass-produced electric vehicles based on batteriesâ€”the fuel cell's technological rival for the zero-emissions mantleâ€”have seen sales slow because their range remains disappointing and their prices high.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I've always thought of battery powered cars as a middle man in the evolution toward hydrogen fuel cells. Undoubtedly, electric cars both convinced people to try something new and made the prospect of owning a zero emission vehicle tangible. But there was no chance for them to become &lt;em&gt;the energy source&lt;/em&gt; for cars. If you want to drive a long distance, what are you going to do? Swap battery packs? Hang out at the diner for a couple hours while your car charges? That isn't practical. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now that the kinks are worked out, I'm excited to see an emergence of hydrogen cars. It will take time to get the price down, but they'll get there.&lt;/p&gt;</summary></entry></feed>